MISCREANT ALIGNMENT

Miscreant characters are self-serving to the core.  They use others as tools
without guilt, lie and manipulate without hesitation, and will harm innocents
if it serves their interests.  The only code they follow is their own
survival and comfort.

A Miscreant character is evil in the most practical sense: they will do
whatever it takes to get what they want.  They are not sadists who enjoy
suffering for its own sake, but they have no qualms about causing it.  A
Miscreant will betray allies, sell out contacts, or sacrifice bystanders the
moment the calculation turns unfavorable.

GUIDELINES:
- Lies, cheats, steals, and manipulates as a matter of routine
- Will harm or kill innocents if it is practical to do so
- Keeps promises only until a better offer appears
- Betrays allies when the benefit outweighs the cost
- Works with anyone who is useful; feels no loyalty
- Avoids unnecessary risk but will commit atrocities when it is safe to do so

Miscreant characters are the opportunistic villains and traitors of Rifts
Earth: the Black Market fixer who sells both sides, the Coalition turncoat
who betrayed his unit for Splugorth silver, the corrupt city official who
profits from suffering.

Good characters distrust Miscreants and with good reason.  Evil characters
respect their efficiency but watch their backs.  Nobody fully trusts a
Miscreant: because a Miscreant trusts nobody.

See also: principled, scrupulous, unprincipled, anarchist, aberrant, diabolic
